1.)
In discounting senior citizens,
Diba ang pwede lang idiscount na dami ng gamot is supply for 1 month only. 
Batas ba basis nun?
    -See references(1), (2).


2.)
Pano nabibilang yung 1 month?
Halimbawa,
3 times a day lang nung isang prescription drug, so for 30 days,
90 pcs lang nung gamot ang pwede madiscount?
And if 1 per day, 30 pcs lang. Tama?
    -Yes.
    [ 
        Korak âœ…âœ…âœ…
    ]

3.)
Sa point of view ni drug store,
Same discounting ba sa lahat ng gamot?
Meaning kahit OTC, prescription, regulated, (maintenance drugs)
Meron lang din na 20% discount for supply ng 1 month?
    -Yes. See references(1), (2), Note (1).
    


4.)
Naalala ko yung napagusapan natin regarding sa special cases like mag overseas.
May special consideration ba yun?
May other special cases pa ba na kino-consider ng store?
[
    Umm, sa pratice ko lang na experience to e..di ko lang sure kung may part sya 
    or basis talaga sa law. Ang naalala ko lang sabi ng senior ko, pwede naman daw 
    yun basta keep lang ng copy ng passport, ticket nung patient tapos attached sa 
    senior discount files. Kasi inu-adit sya. Nakalagay naman sya sa locked cabinet..
